{
  "texts": [
    "Despite these challenges, our examples demonstrate that DL has the potential to detect genomic variations at diverse scales with promising results.Drug response predictions in clinical genomics often rely on data generated via cancer cell line cultures rather than solid tumors.",
    "In pharmacogenomics, genome-wide association studies enable the simultaneous screening of a broad number of cancer-drug pairs and therefore build the foundation for many DL applications.",
    "In 2018, Chang et al. [85] (Fig.",
    "2a) predicted drug efficacy from genomic information of cancer cell lines and drug structural information, whereas Chiu et al. [86] (Fig.",
    "2a) relied on mutation and expression data, without incorporating information about the drug's chemical properties."
  ]
}